	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-23196">
	<article id="article-comment-23196">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Bridie</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">November 26, 2025 at 10:38 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Made it &#8211; loved it. Thank you Dana..</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-23196" data-commentid="23196" data-postid="2296" data-belowelement="article-comment-23196" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Bridie" aria-label="Reply to Bridie">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-10457">
	<article id="article-comment-10457">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Mary Crosby</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">January 03, 2025 at 2:29 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="https://cookwithdana.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Hands down one of the best chicken garlic cream sauces we have done!  The unique spices the chicken was flavored are really nice.  They were wonderful in scrapped into the sauce.  We substituted some of the half and half with skim milk for less calories still creamy with the cheese.  We doubled the garlic, just because we like garlic.  LOL  The cilantro on the top is a lovey bright flavor burst that was not over powering.  Creamy sauce, flavorful chicken, easy to do.  We will do this recipe, again.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-10457" data-commentid="10457" data-postid="2296" data-belowelement="article-comment-10457" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mary Crosby" aria-label="Reply to Mary Crosby">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-cookwdanatest bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-11446">
	<article id="article-comment-11446">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Dana</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">February 03, 2025 at 6:00 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Thanks Mary for giving this recipe a try! This is one of my favorite recipes and I&#8217;m so happy you liked it!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-11446" data-commentid="11446" data-postid="2296" data-belowelement="article-comment-11446" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Dana" aria-label="Reply to Dana">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
